The paper deals with the problem of online multi-object tracking, which is a subfield of computer vision (cs.CV) and has applications in robotics (cs.RO) and machine learning (cs.AI, cs.LG). The proposed method also involves the use of deep convolutional neural networks (cs.MM), which further supports the likelihood of these categories.
